# Error Handling

## API Routes — Always Catch and Return Structured Errors

Every route handler must wrap logic in try/catch. Never let an uncaught exception reach Next.js's default 500 handler.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const { email } = await request.json()
  const { data } = await supabase.from('users').select('*').eq('email', email)
  return NextResponse.json(data)
}

// ✅ GOOD
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  try {
    const { email } = await request.json()
    const { data, error } = await supabase.from('users').select('id, email').eq('email', email).single()
    if (error) return NextResponse.json({ error: error.message }, { status: 400 })
    return NextResponse.json({ user: data })
  } catch {
    return NextResponse.json({ error: ERRORS.INTERNAL }, { status: 500 })
  }
}
```

## Client — Use `getErrorMessage` from `lib/api/client.ts`

Never access `err.message` or `err.response` directly in components. Use the shared helper:

```ts
import { getErrorMessage } from '@/lib/api/client'

try {
  await apiClient.post('/api/auth/login', { email, password })
} catch (err) {
  setError(getErrorMessage(err))
} finally {
  setLoading(false)
}
```

## Validate Inputs at the Top of Every Route

Return early with 400 before touching the database:

```ts
const body = await request.json()
const { email, password } = body

if (!email || !password) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: AUTH.ERRORS.REQUIRED_FIELDS }, { status: 400 })
}
```

## Never Swallow Errors Silently

If you must catch and continue, always log the error:

```ts
// ❌ BAD
try { ... } catch {}

// ✅ GOOD — even a console.error is better than silence during dev;
//    replace with a proper logger (e.g. Sentry, Pino) when adding observability
try { ... } catch (err) { console.error('[context]', err) }
```

## HTTP Status Code Conventions

| Situation | Status |
|-----------|--------|
| Missing / invalid input | 400 |
| Unauthenticated | 401 |
| Forbidden (wrong user) | 403 |
| Resource not found | 404 |
| Conflict (duplicate) | 409 |
| Unexpected server error | 500 |
